question:
District category contains Shopping District, Business District, and Military District.
Supermarkets category contains Blue Apron, and Costco.
The number of each Military District 's Blue Apron equals 21 more than each Business District 's Supermarkets.
The number of each Shopping District 's Blue Apron equals each Military District 's Supermarkets.
The number of each Business District 's Costco equals 19.
How many Supermarkets does Military District have?
solution:
Define each Business District 's Costco as y; So y = 19.
Define each Business District 's Supermarkets as I; So I = y = 19.
Define each Military District 's Blue Apron as L; So L = 21 + I = 21 + 19 = 17.
Define each Military District 's Supermarkets as n; So n = L = 17.
